## Key Differences Between Dev and Prod

| Aspect | Dev (`workflows/dev/`) | Prod (`workflows/prod/`) |
|--------|------------------------|--------------------------|
| Workflow name | `...name [DEV]` | `...name` |
| `active` field | `false` | `true` |
| `id` field | Dev workflow ID | Prod workflow ID |
| Credentials | Sandbox/test credentials | Live credentials |
| Trigger intervals | Manual or longer (1 hour) | Real intervals (15 min) |
| Error handling | Logging only | Alerts enabled |

## Promotion Workflow

When a dev workflow is ready for production:

1. Copy JSON from `dev/` to `prod/`
2. **Remove `[DEV]`** from the `"name"` field
3. **Remove `id`** field (will get new ID on create) or update to prod ID
4. Update credentials to production
5. Set `"active": true`
6. Deploy with `n8n_create_workflow` or `n8n_update_full_workflow`
